The molecular weight of C9H10FNO is 179.18 g/mol. 

Explanation: To calculate the molecular weight of a compound, one must add up the atomic weights of each element in the molecular formula. 
- 9 carbon atoms = 9 x 12.01 g/mol = 108.09 g/mol
- 10 hydrogen atoms = 10 x 1.008 g/mol = 10.08 g/mol
- 1 fluorine atom = 1 x 18.998 g/mol = 18.998 g/mol
- 1 nitrogen atom = 1 x 14.01 g/mol = 14.01 g/mol
- Total molecular weight = 108.09 + 10.08 + 18.998 + 14.01 = 179.18 g/mol
